On November 8, 2018, President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation to honor the victims of the tragic act of violence in Thousand Oaks, California, on November 7, 2018. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at various locations, including the White House, public buildings, military posts and naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government in the District of Columbia and throughout the United States and its Territories and possessions until sunset on November 10, 2018. The flag will also be flown at half-staff at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations, for the same length of time. The proclamation was signed by President Trump on November 8, 2018.